<p class="">There was a question before which I allowed, actually by the hon. Member for Devonport (Mr. Foot) and also by the hon. and gallant Member for Stockport (Wing-Commander Hulbert) which made some comments on a Royal Commission which is now sitting. We may not comment on what is happening before a Royal Commission. If the hon. Member for Devonport is going to comment on something which is done before a Royal Commission which is now sitting and which is still <em>sub judice</em>, that is a matter which is out of Order and I ought not to allow it.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
